Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved, core and seeds removed) and discard the core and seeds. Chop into small pieces. Trim the @spring onion{1%trimmed and thinly sliced} and thinly slice. Halve the @red chilli{1/2%halved lengthways, deseeded and finely chopped} lengthways, deseed then finely chop. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest and halve the @lime{1/2%zested and halved}. Drain and cut the @firm tofu{280%g}(cut into 2cm chunks) into 2cm small chunks.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat. Add the pepper, garlic, chilli and half the spring onion. Stir fry and cook for ~{2%minutes}, then add the @Red Thai Style Paste{50%g} and stir together.

> Add less chilli if you don't like spice!

Cook for ~{1%minute}, then pour in the @coconut milk{200%ml} and mix until combined. Add the @vegetable stock powder{1%tsp} along with the boiling @water{700%ml} from your kettle (see ingredients for amount), bring to a simmer.

Stir in the @peanut butter{1%tbsp} and a pinch of @?sugar{pinch} (if you have some) to your pan. Simmer gently for ~{10%minutes}. Taste the laksa and season to taste with @salt{}, @pepper{} and sugar.

Meanwhile, pop the @cornflour{20%g} and lime zest in a #bowl{} and season with lots of salt and black pepper. Add the tofu to the bowl. Toss the tofu in the cornflour to evenly coat. Heat a splash of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the tofu cubes. Season with salt and pepper. Fry, turning every couple of minutes until crisp and golden on all sides, ~{6-8%minutes}.

When the laksa has been cooking for 10 mins, add in the @egg noodle nest{2}. Gradually break up with a #wooden spoon{} as they soften. Cook until soft enough to eat, about ~{4%minutes}.

> The noodles may soak up some of the coconutty liquid. If this is the case, just add a splash of hot water to get it back to a soupy consistency.

Remove from the heat and add half the lime juice. Taste and add salt, pepper and more lime juice if you feel it needs it. Serve immediately in big bowls topped with the crispy tofu, @coriander{} and the remaining spring onion. Enjoy!